        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-rose-600 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">‚ùå No Pricing Visible = 73% Skip = "Can't Afford, Why Inquire?"</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">"Contact for Quote" = couples assume expensive, don't want awkward conversation if they can't afford. Clear packages = they know budget, only inquire if serious. I saw photographer add "8-Hour Wedding: $3,500" with what's included ‚Üí 61% more qualified inquiries, 3x more bookings. Visible pricing = can afford = serious = book you.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-rose-600 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">‚ùå Vague "Documentary Style" = 79% Think "Generic, No Unique Vision"</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Every photographer says "documentary" or "candid." Couples need specifics: What's your approach? Light & romantic? Bold & dramatic? Fine art? Film vs digital? Editing style? Vague = no unique vision = skip to someone with clear style. I saw photographer add "Candid & Documentary: Emotional Moments, Natural Interactions, Storytelling Focus" ‚Üí 5x more qualified bookings. Style visible = matches our vision = hire you.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-rose-600 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">‚ùå No Availability Calendar = 67% Wasted Inquiries (Booked Dates)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Couples inquire without knowing if you're available. You're booked on their date = wasted time for both. Visible calendar = they check availability first = only inquire if open. I saw photographer add availability calendar ‚Üí 67% fewer wasted inquiries, more time for qualified leads. Calendar = efficient = serious couples only = book you.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-rose-600 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">‚ùå No Couple Testimonials = 69% Think "No Experience, No Trust"</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Couples need proof: Do you deliver on time? Are you professional? Do couples love their photos? Hidden = no experience = risky. I saw photographer add testimonials with wedding photos: "Our photos are absolutely stunning!" ‚Üí 73% more qualified inquiries. Real couples + real photos = trust = hire you.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-rose-600 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">‚ùå No Real Weddings Blog = 87% Miss Referral Traffic</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Vendors (venues, planners, florists) refer photographers they see online. Blog posts with real weddings = vendor visibility = more referrals. Hidden = invisible to vendors = no referrals. I saw photographer add Real Weddings blog ‚Üí 3x more organic traffic, 2x more vendor referrals. Blog = visible = in demand = referrals = bookings.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

